My lady said "Yes" on The Black Sand of the Diamond Beach of South Iceland. 
💍💎♥️.
.
The “diamonds” on Iceland's Diamond Beach refer to pieces of 1,000-year-old icebergs that calved off from the Breiðamerkurjökull glacier, which is an outlet glacier of the largest icecap in Europe – Vatnajökull.
The beauty of Diamond Beach is that it is a 365-day-a-year phenomenon. The ice in the lagoon and the glacier is constantly breaking away into the sea, meaning that there are always new ice diamonds being washed up on the shore. This means that you can go there any time of the year and find new ice diamonds.

You know my love of sheep from my other posts but these are officially the best sheep ever! Valais black nose sheep from Switzerland! And you can visit them and feed them gingernut biscuits, cuddle them and just lose yourself in there cute company. Lots of other brilliant characters on this farm include alpacas, llamas, rabbits horses, guinea pigs. So if you want to enrich your life with being close up and personal with these beautiful animals then book a visit to @ivydenealpacas where you can donate some money in return for all this fun. ♥️🐑🐏 #blacknosesheep #valaisblacknosesheep #ivydenealpacas #alpacas

A little flashback to our visit to Skogafoss in Iceland. Absolutely perfect conditions and not too busy either. This was about 11am in the morning. There's also a hidden gem of a hike when you clime the stairs to the top. Don't just stop at the viewing point above this waterfall. Go on the hike the carries on behind its for about 3 miles out and back. It's amazing with soo many other waterfalls attached to the same stretch of water.  #iceland #icelandtravel #waterfall #skogafoss #skogafosswaterfall #icelandic #landscapephotography

A fun little trek around whinlatter woods to try out a carry bag for Dennis, as he's injured himself or his arthritis has flared up. We're still trying to find out which one it is of the two. Thanks to the awesome staff member of @podgypaws who was a great help fitting and showing us how to get Dennis safely in it. 
We just can't bare to not have him with us on our walks when his leg is playing up. So we got him a K9 Sport Sack which worked great. Though I may now have to join a gym to carry the little monkey. Walking up hill with a Dennis on your back puts a bit of colour in your cheeks for sure 😄 @k9sportsack #podgypaws #podgypawspetshop #k9sportsack #hiking #lakedistrictnationalpark #keswick
